description: I am now offering Telehealth appointments. Change is hard. When you’re in the middle of a life transition, it’s easy to feel lost. Heading off to college or a new career, going through a divorce or a newly 'empty nest', questioning your religious faith or your sexuality are just some of the things that can make you feel like you’re not sure who you are anymore. Maybe you want to make a change but can’t figure out what direction you want to go in. We all need guidance sometimes.

I specialize in working with adult women with specific training in maternal mental health. My focus is on providing a therapy space where clients can feel supported, gently-challenged and deeply-seen. I consider this work sacred and extraordinary. I'm often amazed by the changes my clients experience when they commit to themselves.

I strive to create an environment where my clients will feel safe, valued, and heard. I focus on developing a strong therapeutic alliance which sets the foundation of our work. I specialize in working with bipolar disorder, anxiety disorders, mood disorders, trauma-related issues, relationships, stress management, transitions, grief and loss, self-esteem, and personal growth.

Are you feeling stressed, anxious, overwhelmed, or having relationship problems? Have you tried therapy before that didn't work? Are you drinking too much or using substances and feeling depressed? You can change the way you feel and improve your life.

Are you feeling overwhelmed in your relationship, or struggling with communication? Perhaps you are dealing with a life-changing event? I help individuals and couples to overcome their challenges and find more fulfillment and success in their everyday life.

I work with teens and adults to provide a safe space to step out of the chaos of life and sort through current struggles. I help with stress, anxiety, depression, negative self-talk, low self-esteem and self-worth, self injury, and trauma.
I especially enjoy working with young adults, women in transition, and queer or questioning folks. I’m a mother, wife, and dog-mom who can neither whistle nor swim.

Welcome! I specialize in helping kids, teens, college-age students and young professionals manage anxiety, depression, anger, low self-esteem, social skill difficulties, lack of coping methods, relationship issues, school and work stress.
Hi there! A new year and another opportunity for a new beginning. I work with teens and adults. I specialize in treating OCD, anxiety, depression, trauma, and major life events.
If you are struggling at home with power struggles, tantrums, big emotions feeling out of control, or an event has occurred where you want extra support, I am here to meet you where you are.
Does your child get frustrated easily with homework? Guess frequently at words? Have poor handwriting? Read slowly or inaccurately? Lack self-esteem? Dislike reading? I can help!
I am a licensed psychotherapist and wellness advocate who believes in focusing on the mind-body connection for a holistic approach to healing.
I offer a safe, fast, and effective combination of hypnotherapy and life coaching to help every client gain relief from mental and physical suffering.
As an Addiction Social Worker, I specialize in empowering individuals to recover from addictive behaviors via support and counseling.
Are you someone who prefers the convenience of tele-health services to in-person counseling? Are you suffering with anxiety and/or depression?

I specialize in working with women who are struggling with issues such as anxiety, depression, adjusting to life transitions, grief, family/relationship challenges, low self-esteem, prenatal/postpartum concerns, pregnancy loss, and infertility.
